<% count = @accesses.count %>
<% this = (count > 1) ? "These" : "This" # According to Rails, the singular of 'this' is 'thare'. %>
<% target_display_login = "@#{@target.display_login}" %>
Hey <%= @user.display_login %>,

An administrator in the <%= target_display_login %> organization has denied your fine-grained personal access token <%= "request".pluralize(count) %>.

<% @accesses.each do |access| %>
  - <%= access.name %>
<% end %>

<% if @reason %>
  The access was denied because <%= @reason %>.
<% end %>

<%= "#{this} token".pluralize(count) %> cannot be used against the <%= target_display_login %> organization.

If you run into problems, please contact support by visiting <%= contact_url %>

Thanks,
The GitHub Team
